name: READY TO ROCK Black Frame
description:
Roxanne was quite unlike the daughter her parents had expected. She was always a trouble-making kid and would get sent to the principal’s office seemingly daily, she cared little for her academics and her grades suffered as a result, she brought home every undesirable type of boy from sleazy to violent. Her only talent was playing the bass — something her parents despised.

As her high school life went by, she felt increasingly unhappy with everything about it. She often felt depressed, lonely and miserable — but there wasn't anything worse than feeling unappreciated… and there was nobody there to appreciate her. She never had any real friends, she knew that all of the boys she brought home simply said they liked her music to try and get in her pants, a fact she was disgusted with.  It's also not like her family shared her love for rock music — since she was a kid, they had been telling her to find a "real" career path and stay in school, something she just couldn’t seem to hold down. Roxanne knew what she had to do — she needed to take matters into her own hands!

Immediately following that thought, she took to the internet and searched for any audition that she could find. An interesting one popped up: "wanted, a bassist for a virtual idol band". The idea of it was definitely an oddball one, but one that she knew she had to apply. She had never heard of this character, but the demo reel of the idol’s music sounded exactly like the rock she had always wanted to play!

Roxanne had the overwhelming feeling that she and this virtual idol were destined to play music together and be world-famous. The only thing that could calm her down was playing the bass, so she grabbed it and did a grand powerslide along the carpet to release some of her bubbling energy before heading out to pack for the audition. "I'm gonna rock this!”

—-

The Gallery Gehenna Project is a daily art project where there are multiple frames for each individual artwork, each with different types of rarity applied. Black frames are initially given out for free on Hicetnunc. All artworks will be compatible within the Gallery Gehenna Game with each artwork unlocking a playable story segment.
